{"General": {"Code": "MRLN", "Type": "Common Stock", "Name": "Merlin, Inc.", "Exchange": "NASDAQ", "CurrencyCode": "USD", "CurrencyName": "US Dollar", "CurrencySymbol": "$", "CountryName": "USA", "CountryISO": "US", "OpenFigi": "BBG01R1Y9TJ0", "ISIN": "US5901061003", "LEI": null, "PrimaryTicker": "MRLN.US", "CUSIP": null, "CIK": null, "EmployerIdNumber": null, "FiscalYearEnd": "December", "IPODate": "2003-11-12", "InternationalDomestic": null, "Sector": "Industrials", "Industry": "Aerospace & Defense", "GicSector": null, "GicGroup": null, "GicIndustry": null, "GicSubIndustry": null, "HomeCategory": null, "IsDelisted": false, "Description": "Merlin, Inc. develops AI-powered autonomous flight software and systems for aircraft in the United States and New Zealand. The company provides an aircraft-agnostic, AI-powered software platform that enables autonomous flight for both legacy and next-generation airborne systems. Its main product, the Merlin Pilot, is an integrated hardware and software solution that manages navigation, communication with air traffic control, obstacle avoidance, and real-time decision-making using sensor technologies and natural language processing. The company supports both military and civil aviation programs, offering solutions for missions such as cargo transport and national security operations. It collaborates with partners and regulatory bodies to conduct flight trials and support the certification of autonomous flight systems. The company serves defense organizations, commercial aviation clients, government agencies, regulators, and air cargo operators. The company was founded in 2018 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts.", "Address": "129 South Street, Boston, MA, United States, 02111", "AddressData": {"Street": "129 South Street", "City": "Boston", "State": "MA", "Country": "United States", "ZIP": "02111"}, "Listings": {}, "Officers": {"0": {"Name": "Matthew  George", "Title": "Founder, President, CEO, Treasurer, Secretary & Chairman of